<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-13T11:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-13T11:36:00-05:00" n="590" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d590">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17456</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Querétaro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-13T10:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1916, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>During conference with Secretary Foreign Relations this morning he stated
                            to me: “Should war result over the Columbus affair the position of the
                            United States would be that of assisting the reactionaries as against
                            the Constitutionalist Government.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Belt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>